Kaggle Facial Keypoints Detection Project¶

Kaggle page

Two Different Sets of Images¶

The dataset is composed of two different sets of images with a different number of keypoints.

Inspection of these sets of images, suggests slightly different definitions for certain keypoints by set, e.g., nose tip.

efg, 2015-11-29.

Setup¶

Starts with file kaggle-facial-keypoints-data.Rd created in Step A, Getting Started.

In [1]:
time1 <- Sys.time()          
cat(format(time1, "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"), "\n")

source("efg-imagelib.R")

"d" for data and "im" for images in the following variables.

Test Set¶

The submission file specifies the number of features associated with each test image.

In [6]:
d <- read.csv("C:/Kaggle/2015/Facial-Keypoints/data/submissionFileFormat.csv", as.is=TRUE)
d <- d[,-ncol(d)]
In [7]:
library(plyr)    # ddply
testSummary <- ddply(d, .(ImageId), summarize, counts=length(ImageId))
countsTest <- testSummary$counts  
table(countsTest)
Out[7]:
countsTest
   6    8   18   20   22   24   26   28   30 
   2 1190    1    2    2    3    9   18  556

Potential Problem Images¶

Train images with other than 30 features, or Test images with other than 8 features may be problems. Let's take a look ...

Features Counts / 2 = Points

6 Features / 3 Points¶

In [10]:
par(mfrow=c(4,4), mar=c(1,1,1,1))
ShowTrainImages( which(countsTrain == 6) )

par(mfrow=c(2,2), mar=c(1,1,1,1))
ShowTestImages( which(countsTest == 6) )
